        <div><<printHTML `toggle(v => settings.OpenAIGeneration = v, settings.OpenAIGeneration)`>></div>
    </div>

    <button class="dark-btn obsidian" onclick="SugarCube.Engine.backward()">Back</button>
</div>


:: Local AI Image Guide [start nobr]

<div class="abyss-credits-block" style="margin-left: -5%; margin-right: -5%; padding: 40px; background: rgba(42, 42, 42, 0.75);">
<h2>Local AI Image Guide</h2>

    <div class="abyss-api-notice">
        You can now generate AI portraits locally on your own computer using ComfyUI! This allows you to create portraits without paying for API credits, though it requires more setup and computer resources.
    </div>

    <div class="abyss-api-steps">
        <h3>One-Click Installer Instructions</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to the local-gen folder in your Abyss Diver installation directory.</li>

            <li>Run the appropriate installer file for your operating system:
                <ul>
                    <li>Windows: Run "one-click-comfyui.bat"</li>
                    <li>Linux/Mac: Run "one-click-comfyui.sh"</li>
                </ul>
            </li>

            <li>Wait for the disk space prompt. The installer will begin by setting up git, python, pip, and required packages.</li>

            <li>When prompted about required disk space, press Enter to confirm and continue.</li>

            <li>The download process will begin - you'll see progress updates for every 10% completed.</li>

            <li>Once ComfyUI installs with its components, it will start the ComfyUI and proxy code, and you will receive a prompt on whether they succeded in loading!</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="abyss-api-warning">
        GPU Support: Windows users need an NVIDIA graphics card. Linux users can use any GPU, and Mac users can optionally use Metal CPU but requires some manual work.<br><br>
        You will need at least 22GB of disk space available for ComfyUI and the required models to be downloaded.<br><br>
        It is recommended you have a graphics card with at least 4GB of VRAM for Windows. For graphics cards older than the 1060, please say yes to othe option when it shows up.
    </div>

    <div class="abyss-api-steps">
        <h3>Final Setup</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>There will be a message saying whether "Cannot connect to the proxy..." or "Cannot connect to ComfyUI...". This means the install failed and the log needs to be looked at.</li>
            <li>The message "Successfully connected to both ComfyUI and the Proxy! Head to Abyss Diver and open the AI Portrait page!" will tell you that the generator is ready.
            <li>Open your Abyss Diver Settings and enable ComfyUI generation</li>
            <li>Visit the AI Portrait Passage - you should see "ComfyUI Available" in green text</li>
            <li>You're now ready to generate portraits!</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="abyss-api-steps">
        <h3>Troubleshooting</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>"git" is not recognized:</strong> Install git from https://git-scm.com/downloads </li>

            <li><strong>"python" commands not working:</strong> Install Python 3.11.9 from https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-3119/ </li>

            <li>For any other issues, please read the webpage https://github.com/FloricSpacer/AbyssDiver/blob/preview/local-gen/LocalDOCS.md as it contains the up-to-date troubleshooting guide.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

     <p>If you have any questions, feel free to ask on our Discord server. And you're very welcome to share any especially good portraits you get!</p>

